<font color="#FF0000">TO COOK BARELA</font><br>
<tt>Sat Jun 28 18:11:58 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
Cook,<br><br>
This is a place where you may share your memories of your service in Vietnam, and I may share mine.<br><br>
Your opinions and my opinions are different. <br><br>
The incident I described shouldn't have happened - given the circumstances. I stand by what I said.<br><br>
I think that your comments are very compelling, yet once again your opinions are not the same as mine. <br><br>
Like you I am glad that those who served in Vietnam are finally receiving recognition for their accomplishments. However, and I am speaking for myself, any accomplishments or any &quot;proving of myself&quot; will always be put into a lesser perspective when weighed against the suffering of the Vietnamese people in a war that should never have happened.
<p><code>-- wingman@greene.xtn.net  (Tom Dier) </code><p>


